results.name: Decimal expansion of the absolute value of zeta'''(2), the third derivative of the Riemann zeta function at 2.
reference: B. K. Choudhury, The Riemann zeta-function and its derivatives, Proc. R. Soc. Lond. A (1995) 450, 477-499
formula: Equals 3! +sum_{k>=0} (-1)^k*gamma(3+k)/k!, where gamma(.) are the Stieltjes constants A001620, A082633, A086279 etc. [Choudhury, Thm. 4]
results.author: _R. J. Mathar_, Dec 07 2011
